  "texts": [
    "Zacharis et al. [20] described a novel method for automating the creation of structured cybersecurity exercise scenarios.",
    "Their proposed work included Machine Learning (ML), more especially Name Entity Recognition (NER), to evaluate unstructured data and provide meaningful, structured scenarios for cybersecurity training.",
    "The document describes the creation and implementation of a unique ontology, the cyber exercise scenario ontology, which aims to structure created content in a way that is both machine and human-readable.",
    "Their research methodology intends to increase the speed, quality, and relevance of cybersecurity exercise scenarios scenario development, primarily aiding exercise planners with little experience in scenario building.",
    "These exercises are crucial in enabling IT professionals and cybersecurity teams to effectively prevent and mitigate cyber threats."
